    "content": "--اَللّٰهُمَّ صَلِّ عَلٰى مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ عَلِيِّ بْنِ مُوْسٰى عَلَمِ التُّقٰى وَ نُوْرِ الْهُدٰى وَ مَعْدِنِ الْوَفَاۤءِ وَ فَرْعِ الْاَزْكِيَاۤءِ وَ خَلِيْفَةِ الْاَوْصِيَاۤءِ وَ اَمِيْنِكَ عَلٰى وَحْيِكَ اَللّٰهُمَّ فَكَمَا هَدَيْتَ بِهِ مِنَ الضَّلَالَةِ وَ اسْتَنْقَذْتَ بِهِ مِنَ الْحَيْرَةِ وَ اَرْشَدْتَ بِهِ مَنِ اهْتَدٰى وَ زَكَّيْتَ بِهِ مَنْ تَزَكّٰى فَصَلِّ عَلَيْهِ اَفْضَلَ مَا صَلَّيْتَ عَلٰىۤ اَحَدٍ مِنْ اَوْلِيَاۤئِكَ وَ بَقِيَّةِ اَوْصِيَاۤئِكَ اِنَّكَ عَزِيْزٌ حَكِيْمٌ۔", 
    "audio": "", 
    "transliteration": "", 
    "english": "O Allah, (please) send blessings upon Muhammad the son of ‘Ali the son of Müsâ, the epitome of piety, the illumination of true guidance, the essence of faithfulness, the branch of the bright ones, the vicegerent of the Successors, and Your trustee on Your revelations. O Allah, as You have guided through him against straying off, saved against confusion, directed those who were rightly guided, and purified those who were purified, so also (please) bless him with the most favorite blessings that You have ever conferred upon any of Your intimate servants and agents of Your Successors. Verily, You are Almighty, All-wise."
}